snippet: No charges will be brought against Ernesto Pulido, a tree trimmer in Oakland who knocked five baby herons from their nests a month ago while trimming trees for the United States Postal Service.
abstract: Ernesto Pulido, tree trimmer in Oakland, Calif, will not face charges for knocking five baby herons from their nest while trimming trees for the United States Postal Service.
lead_paragraph: No charges will be brought against Ernesto Pulido, a tree trimmer in Oakland who knocked five baby herons from their nests a month ago while trimming trees for the United States Postal Service.

headline.main: California: Tree Trimmer Won’t Be Charged
headline.print_headline: California: Tree Trimmer Won’t Be Charged
